1.5k hours I can never get back. 

Amazon Game Studios have had every opportunity in the last 2 years to get their $#!@ together, but nothing has changed. 

The game is still a buggy mess, there is nothing the developers touch that isn't worse off than before, the design decisions are absurd and there is frequent and recurring immoral practices in place, as to what is communicated and when (if at all), to take advantage of players. 

Based on my experiences and time in game, I can say with absolute certainty:
     * No one from Amazon Game Studios are gamers, nor do they play their own game;
     * No one from Amazon Game Studios has any real MMO experience, either as a developer or player;
     * Amazon Game Studios is completely divorced from reality, it seems they exist in their own hyper-insular bubble that is totally disconnected from the real world;
     * Your time, as a player, will not be respected - if anything, it will be abused. 

If Amazon Game Studios weren't being propped up by the broader Amazon group, it would have gone under shortly after release. I am disgusted companies like this continue to exist and push such appalling quality products & services. 

Do not buy this game or support this company; it is & they are, a blight on the industry and an absolute joke.

4/10 - Launch experience wasn't good.

- Very poor server management - extremely long queues that quickly turned into desolated servers;
- Very glitch and exploitable bugs;
- Repetitive gameplay;
- Uninspired enemy design;

The game has some fun aspects, but can't recommend it's current state. I never returned to play after this, but I heard the game got improved, so who knows.

Linux Mint Cinnamon 19.3, NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3050, 32 GB system RAM

A buddy raved about this game (he uses Windows) and I have seen reports on the web that NW does work in Linux, so I gave it a try.  Spent a couple of hours trying a lot of different things to make this work, finally gave up.  Either the game would freeze with a white screen on startup, then (sometimes) crash to desktop, or the game would play for a few minutes, then CtD.

If I deleted the New World folders from the AGS folders in Roaming and Local folders, I could play for about five minutes, then another crash to desktop.

After all my testing, I ended up with one lvl 3 char on NA East and one lvl 2 char on NA West.

List of what I tried includes:
Started with files installed on HDD, then used Steam to move files to SSD, repeatedly verified files;
Four different versions of Proton, including GE Proton;
Three different NVIDIA graphics drivers, beginning with the 525 that I use constantly for Path of Exile, then tried 545 (sorta beta) and finally 535;
Started on NA East server, saw 100ms+ pings, switched to NA West (sub-20ms);
Full screen and windowed;
Numerous reboots and cleaning of AGS folders;
Setting Steam launch options to: -high -useallavailablecores;
Also tried Steam launch options to force DirectX10, 11, and 12.

I'm done.  If my experience is typical for Linux players, this game is NOT ready for release to Linux.  Requested a refund from Steam.

---------------------
Update: Steam refused my refund request, claiming my account showed I had played the game for four hours.  No, I did not play the game for four hours.  I spent four hours trying to get this POS to run more than five minutes without crashing, then finally gave up.  Linux users, you've been warned.

Tried giving this game another shot, amazed that they locked it behind a paywall, simply disrespectful.
You're in a huge disadvantage against other players that paid for the ""expansion"", they'll have thing like: 
- mounts, which straight up turns open world PVP inviable if you don't have one;
- higher level cap that translates to higher attributes (more damage, health, etc.);
- higher gear score items with better stats;
- and an exclusive weapon (new weapons used to be avaible to all players).

Such a shame, this game had an incredible potential, really sad to see it going to the generic MMO path, in which they create a problem and sell you a "solution".
